**🎯 UNIFIED SEARCH – EINE SUCHBOX FÜR ALLES (YouTube, Podcast, Radio):**

---

## 🎬 STRATEGIE

User tippt **ein Keyword** → Backend sucht parallel:
- **YouTube:** Videos über Google-Suche (site:youtube.com)
- **Podcasts:** RSS/Podcast-APIs (ListenNotes, RadioPublic)
- **Radio:** RadioBrowser API (kostenlos!)

**Ergebnis:** Alle 3 Typen in einem Grid, Player passt sich automatisch an.

---

## 🔍 SEARCH-METHODEN

### 1️⃣ YouTube (Kein API-Key nötig)
```javascript
// Google-Suche nach YouTube-Videos
const youtubeQuery = `${userQuery} site:youtube.com`;
const resultsHTML = await googleSearch(youtubeQuery);
// Extrahiere: Title, Thumbnail, Video-ID
```

### 2️⃣ Podcasts (API-basiert)
```javascript
// Option A: ListenNotes (kostenlos mit Limits)
const podcast = await fetch(`https://listen-api.listennotes.com/api/v2/search?q=${query}&type=episode`);

// Option B: RadioPublic API
const podcast = await fetch(`https://radiopublic.com/api/v2/podcasts?q=${query}`);
```

### 3️⃣ Radio (Kostenlos!)
```javascript
// RadioBrowser API – kostenlos, keine Keys
const radio = await fetch(`https://de1.api.radio-browser.info/json/stations/byname?name=${query}`);
// Returns: name, url_resolved, country, homepage
```

---

## ⚠️ CORS & SCRAPING-PROBLEME

**Google-Scraping direkt im Browser:** ❌ Blockiert (CORS)
**Lösung:** Backend-Proxy in server.js nutzen

```javascript
app.get('/api/unified-search', async (req, res) => {
  const query = req.query.q;

  // Parallel suchen
  const [videos, podcasts, radio] = await Promise.all([
    searchYoutube(query),
    searchPodcasts(query),
    searchRadio(query)
  ]);

  res.json({ videos, podcasts, radio });
});
```

---

## 📊 ERGEBNIS-FORMAT

```json
{
  "videos": [
    { "videoId": "dQw4w9WgXcQ", "title": "...", "thumbnail": "...", "channel": "..." }
  ],
  "podcasts": [
    { "title": "...", "description": "...", "audioUrl": "...", "episodeTitle": "..." }
  ],
  "radio": [
    { "name": "SWR3", "country": "DE", "streamUrl": "http://...", "favicon": "..." }
  ]
}
```

---

## 🎮 PLAYER-LOGIK

- **YouTube → iFrame Player**
- **Podcast/Radio → HTML5 Audio** (mit play/pause/seek)

